<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1767,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1876,1901]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1763" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1763" box="[446,676,1876,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Ceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[446,510,1876,1899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Ceria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Scopoli, J. A." box="[519,676,1876,1901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="1" refId="ref5527" refString="Scopoli, J. A. (1763) Entomologia Carniolica exhibens insecta Carnioliae indigena et distributa in ordines, genera, species, varietates. Methodo Linnaeana. I. T. Trattner, Vindobonae [= Vienna], [30] + 420 + [1] pp." type="journal article" year="1763">Scopoli, 1763</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was originally proposed for two species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1182,1319,1876,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scatopsidae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="5" refId="ref4677" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1794) Entomologia systematica emendata et aucta. Secundum classes, ordines, genera, species adjectis synonimis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Tom. IV. C. G. Proft, Fil. et Soc., Hafniae [= Copenhagen], [6] + 472 + [5] pp." type="journal article" year="1794">Fabricius (1794)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1763" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1763" box="[454,518,1912,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Ceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[454,518,1912,1935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Ceria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for a species of 
<taxonomicName box="[707,821,1911,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Syrphidae</taxonomicName>
and his usage of the name became widely accepted in pre-1902 literature (P.A. Latreille, J.W. Meigen, J.W. Zetterstedt, G.H. Verrall, etc.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1767,2009]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">
A description of the only included species was given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[839,1027,1984,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="5" refId="ref4677" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1794) Entomologia systematica emendata et aucta. Secundum classes, ordines, genera, species adjectis synonimis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Tom. IV. C. G. Proft, Fil. et Soc., Hafniae [= Copenhagen], [6] + 472 + [5] pp." type="journal article" year="1794">Fabricius (1794)</bibRefCitation>
, but inadvertently the specific name [
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1794" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1795" box="[160,284,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavicornis">
<emphasis box="[160,284,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">clavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] was omitted. It first appeared in an index to the four volumes (1792–1794) of Fabricius’s 
<emphasis box="[151,665,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Entomologia systematica emendata et aucta</emphasis>
prepared by 
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, F." box="[826,989,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" refId="ref5648" refString="Weber, F. (1795) Nomenclator entomologicus. C. E. Bohn, Chilonii et Hamburgii [= Kiel &amp; Hamburg], 171 pp." type="book" year="1795">Weber (1795)</bibRefCitation>
. Accordingly, the authorship of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1794" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1795" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Ceria clavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is correctly attributed to 
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, F." box="[558,712,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" refId="ref5648" refString="Weber, F. (1795) Nomenclator entomologicus. C. E. Bohn, Chilonii et Hamburgii [= Kiel &amp; Hamburg], 171 pp." type="book" year="1795">Weber (1795)</bibRefCitation>
rather than 
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[848,1037,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" pagination="5" refId="ref4677" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1794) Entomologia systematica emendata et aucta. Secundum classes, ordines, genera, species adjectis synonimis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Tom. IV. C. G. Proft, Fil. et Soc., Hafniae [= Copenhagen], [6] + 472 + [5] pp." type="journal article" year="1794">Fabricius (1794)</bibRefCitation>
. This interpretation of 
<typeStatus box="[1293,1341,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">type</typeStatus>
fixation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1794" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1794" box="[181,425,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[181,245,260,283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Ceria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[251,425,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" pagination="5" refId="ref4677" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1794) Entomologia systematica emendata et aucta. Secundum classes, ordines, genera, species adjectis synonimis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Tom. IV. C. G. Proft, Fil. et Soc., Hafniae [= Copenhagen], [6] + 472 + [5] pp." type="journal article" year="1794">Fabricius, 1794</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is the same as that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Sabrosky, C. W." box="[672,900,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref5501" refString="Sabrosky, C. W. (1999) Family-group names in Diptera. An annotated catalog. Myia, 10, 1 - 360." type="journal article" year="1999">Sabrosky (1999: 79)</bibRefCitation>
except that authorship of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1794" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1795" box="[1190,1386,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavicornis">
<emphasis box="[1190,1386,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Ceria clavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was attributed in that work to Fabricius, 1795 not 
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, F." box="[660,804,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" refId="ref5648" refString="Weber, F. (1795) Nomenclator entomologicus. C. E. Bohn, Chilonii et Hamburgii [= Kiel &amp; Hamburg], 171 pp." type="book" year="1795">Weber, 1795</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
